document_data.Known Stutterers and Stammerers:
The following people had persistent stutters or stammers:
* Luckbringer [[Adam]], a priest of [[Tymora]] in [[Ravens Bluff]], had an occasional stutter.<ref>{{Cite organized play/LC/Dragon's Deep|9-10}}
* [[Clacker]], a [[pech]] turned into a [[hook horror]] with a recurring stutter;<ref>
* [[Delitar|Delitar the Slow]], a historian of [[Westgate]] named for his slow, stuttering speech;
* [[Khalid]], a [[half-elf]] [[fighter]] and [[Harper]] who had a recurring strong stutter;
* [[Maddgoth]], a mage and killer based in [[Maddgoth's Castle]] in [[Undermountain]], who had a strong stammer;<ref>
* [[Shulgi]], a [[vampire]] thief operating in [[Unther]] with a stutter;<ref>
* [[Spernik]], a [[Dragon Cult]]ist who stammered when nervous;<ref>{{Cite adventurers league/Tyranny in Phlan|24}}
* [[Yazilliclick]], a [[Sprite (creature)|wood sprite]] of the [[Moonshae Isles]] who stuttered and repeated words often.<ref>
* [[Ellis Adarbrent]], a noble and cartographer of [[Waterdeep]], who stuttered when nervous;
* [[Zo Hillmover]], a [[dwarf]] warrior of the Vast, stuttered when nervous;<ref>{{Cite organized play/LC/Race for the Rod|7}}
* [[Brian Robbinton]], a shepherd of [[the Vast]], stuttered and spoke slowly;<ref>{{Cite organized play/LC/Resolution|4}}
* [[Tym Doeskin]], a leatherworker of [[Ravens Bluff]], who stammered and stuttered because of his shyness;<ref>{{Cite organized play/LC/Invitation to a Wedding|5}}<ref>{{Cite organized play/LC/A Simple Man|6}}<ref>{{Cite organized play/LC/Slaves to Fashion|6}}<ref>{{Cite organized play/LC/Fire's Eye|6}}
* [[Taspar Hatchhill]], a [[wereraven]] who stuttered often, especially when agitated;<ref>
* [[Kalib bin Jabir]] a would-be tomb robber of [[Tajar]], who stuttered in social situations;
* [[Ko La Ko]], a [[wu jen]] or [[Shou Lung]], who stuttered when speaking to large groups;
* [[Chanczlatha Luruin]], a [[cleric]] of [[Lathander]] at the [[Bargewright Inn]], who had a recurring stammer; and<ref><ref>
* [[Marvin Morris]], a.k.a. Marrrrrrvin, a merchant and animal trainer as well as chancellor of the island of [[Gull Easel]], had a heavy stutter.{{Cite organized play/LC/Stairway to Heaven|15}}<ref>{{Cite organized play/LC/Up, Up and Away|10}}
